</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6BBDC0E06822331A3BD9A8A37C3937F7" lastPageId="721" lastPageNumber="722" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="46162A3ACFBA31E48626E96C6483677D" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">
<taxonomicName id="FE4360CE1FA251736637F98AE8B2A861" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Argestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Argestes</taxonomicName>
J.E. LeConte, 1849: 26 [
<emphasis id="76720B1EF45E50A36E2D900AC786A772" italics="true" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">nomen oblitum</emphasis>
, see Bousquet (2008b: 328)]. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="4CA2A66577972B592AB87D893282B31E" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1843" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidulus">
<emphasis id="98CD586B20C0A91E6B82D2F0BB5A851F" italics="true" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">Harpalus nitidulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1843 (= 
<taxonomicName id="8EF2F10F9C25B8AAE70D170F5976A8F7" baseAuthorityName="Csiki" baseAuthorityYear="1932" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis id="F62DBB5FB1A7C9F59597AAE3D7CA8AF3" italics="true" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">Trichotichnus fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Csiki, 1932) by monotypy. Etymology. Name of the north-west wind in classical antiquity. Note. Hardy et al. (1986: 472) argued that the paper in which this name was proposed was written by J.E. LeConte and not his son, J.L. LeConte.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="70D5632F4243AC114007951E876214E7" lastPageId="721" lastPageNumber="722" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">
<taxonomicName id="42779481D28498E440CD8AFE932FA631" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Iridessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iridessus</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1883b: 240. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="7B4CDB4274F98A5CF65D2B214E29B217" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="720" pageNumber="721" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">
<emphasis id="0F6A03FD96DFCA976ABA7FA2F791DF7B" italics="true" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">Harpalus lucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Morawitz, 1863 designated by Habu (1954a: 245). Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Latin 
<emphasis id="2AE6367E11E6D8E87A5603BA2589376C" italics="true" pageId="720" pageNumber="721">iris</emphasis>
(rain 
<pageBreakToken id="F2CE856BE347EEA4378AF5D5BB4D737A" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" start="start">bow</pageBreakToken>
) and the French noun 
<emphasis id="17362C222DC24F121F69D0845854A10B" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">dessus</emphasis>
(above), alluding to the iridescence on the elytra of adults of the species included by Bates in this taxon [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECE0D9CA2F033D8BB179F31DEF9E5D32" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">
<taxonomicName id="7764027877EC4AA79D56F3DC8A4B4528" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Episcopellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Episcopellus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1914: 235. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="263CEABD9E1180DBEA0B86CA62F5B092" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autumnalis">
<emphasis id="353888BEC98E82F8AED64AB6FDC03EB2" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Feronia autumnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823 by original designation. Synonymy established by Ball and Bousquet (2000: 96). Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="3DA235BEE4B14495E5493814C86965B6" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">episcopos</emphasis>
(overseer) and the suffix - 
<emphasis id="DC7C9A9F5E663EFC5F758257A247B32A" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">ellus</emphasis>
(small, little) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A655BC9D76E66C54C92F41588EB3BDFC" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="FD87BB406C1BB63CF7BAC1E21E4C6B8E" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B948877E143514BC8095563973569C19" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Six species in the Nearctic (two species) and east Palaearctic (four species) Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33974B5A98F20FD34D3B77DFB428CC50" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="A1848A7C0CC6541CCE7ABBE27FBD2060" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C47929A9D4FE066ED7529A11CD8C27CB" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">
Kataev (in Ball and Bousquet 2000: 96) revalidated 
<taxonomicName id="C7C83C7FD57F01F81CDE0A345B818F82" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Iridessus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6783BA05820A637F8F53EAC6E40C5ED6" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Iridessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates as a subgenus, considered by most authors as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A7B4EB8E73E9F2B3D586801D67A2141B" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1863" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="721" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB9210EB638DBE829FD3C35E74FCB947" italics="true" pageId="721" pageNumber="722">Trichotichnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
